Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.58,0:03:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,進來
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.65,0:03:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馮先生  時間到了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.27,0:03:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一萬
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.70,0:03:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走吧
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.86,0:03:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向阿波馬托克斯最後的血腥進軍在這裏發起\NHere began the last bloody march toward Appomattox
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而格蘭特將軍與李將軍就在那裏首次碰面\Nwhere General Grant met General Lee for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.73,0:03:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勇敢的人們用鮮血鑄就歷史\NAnd brave men bled, set the course of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.79,0:03:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很榮幸能夠來到這裏\NI'm so honored to be here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.04,0:03:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,紀念陸路戰役150週年\Ncelebrating the 150th anniversary of the Overland Campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.11,0:03:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感謝郡長羅伯茨\NThank you to County Administrator Roberts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:03:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感謝所有熱忱的情景重現演員\Nto all the dedicated re-enactors,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.24,0:03:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,當然  還要感謝\Nand, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.16,0:03:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奧基弗州長組織了如此精彩的三日活動\Nto Governor O'Keefe for organizing such a wonderful three-day event.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.74,0:03:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說完了嗎  先生\NOh. That's all, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.67,0:03:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說完了  短小精悍\NThat's it. Short and sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.31,0:04:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至少很短小\NOr at least it's short.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.74,0:04:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加夫尼的人稱內戰為"北方侵略戰爭"\NIn Gaffney, people called it the "War of Northern Aggression."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.55,0:04:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,個人而言  我並不以南部邦聯為榮\NI personally take no pride in the Confederacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.07,0:04:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打不贏的仗就不要打\NAvoid wars you can't win,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.41,0:04:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更不要為奴隸制這樣愚蠢的原因而戰\Nand never raise your flag for a asinine cause like slavery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.28,0:04:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他就來  -好\N- He's on his way. - Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.40,0:04:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人們會忘記這事的\NPeople will move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.28,0:04:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不會的  你說的越少  他們越會去挖掘\NThey won't. The less you say, the more they'll dig.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.21,0:04:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就讓他們挖\NLet them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.10,0:04:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,薇拉  能讓我們單獨待會兒嗎\NWilla, could you give us two seconds?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.46,0:04:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就在外面\NI'll be right outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.72,0:04:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,麥金尼斯的事發生在大學時期\NMcGinnis happened in college.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.35,0:04:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,墮胎則是五年之後的事\NThe abortion happened five years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.58,0:04:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有留下任何病歷\NThere aren't any medical records.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完全沒有嗎\NNone at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.30,0:04:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們特別確保了這一點\NWe specifically made sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,護士呢  等候室的人呢\NA nurse? Somebody in the waiting room?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.44,0:04:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有醫生一個人在場\NThe doctor was the only one there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.96,0:04:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那他現在在哪裏\NThen where is he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.10,0:05:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已經是很久以前的事了  康納  他去世了\NIt's a long time ago, Connor. He passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我都不擔心  那你也不必\NAnd if I'm not worried, you shouldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算如此  性侵的事現在成為焦點了\NEven still, sexual assault is part of the conversation now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.70,0:05:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有的文章和專欄都會提到你\NEvery article and column mentions you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.67,0:05:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我們不提供素材  就無法塑造你的形象\NIf we offer nothing, we can't shape your image.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我說的很清楚  我不想曝光\NI made it very clear I don't want exposure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.04,0:05:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等我們有新東西可說的時候  我們再說\NWhen we have something new to say, we'll say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.76,0:05:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,薇拉  參謀長聯席會議那邊怎麼樣了\NWilla. Any luck with the Joint Chiefs?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.84,0:05:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席辦公室還是說他沒空\NThe Chairman's Office still says he's unavailable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.99,0:05:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他們說可以派參謀部主任過來\NBut they did offer to send the Director of the Joint Staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.59,0:05:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明天上午11點\N11:00 a.m. tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.67,0:05:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,定下來\NConfirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們去白宮西樓弗蘭西斯的辦公室見\NWe'll meet in Francis' office at the West Wing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.94,0:05:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還有別的事嗎\NAnything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.69,0:05:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒了  我該出發了\NNo. I should get going, hit the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.99,0:05:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝你  康納\NThank you, Connor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.61,0:05:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接通布魯克斯議員女士的電話\NGet Congresswoman Brooks on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.53,0:05:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看第一夫人今天下午是否有空\NAnd see if the First Lady will be available this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.07,0:05:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想要給中國所有參加峰會的人做簡報嗎\NYou want a brief on everyone on the Chinese side of the Summit?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.43,0:05:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  杜蘭特在華盛頓做的只是表面功夫\NNo. What Durant's doing in Washington is just the facade.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.41,0:05:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這可是真正的談判\NThis is the real negotiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.28,0:05:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你手上關於馮的資料都給我\NGive me what you have on Feng.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.89,0:06:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馮山德  家族在共產黨內很有影響\NXander Feng. Deep family connections to the Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.56,0:06:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他祖父曾跟毛澤東肩並肩作戰\NGrandfather fought side by side with Mao.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.96,0:06:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在電信業勢力很大\NBig in the telecom industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.37,0:06:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,淨資產估計有五百億\NEstimated net worth is over 50 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.01,0:06:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比雷蒙德還有錢\NMore than Raymond's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.54,0:06:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多幾十億  但誰在乎呢\NBy a few billion. But who's counting?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除了稀土金屬精煉廠之外\NDo they have any other business partnerships
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.79,0:06:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們還有其他商業合作嗎\Nother than the Rare Earth Refinery?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.88,0:06:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我沒有發現\NNot that I could find.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.00,0:06:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  向杜蘭特詢問一下進度\NAll right. Get a progress update from Durant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.95,0:06:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告訴她我們一得知馮的要求就通知她\NTell her I'll be in touch as soon as we know what Feng wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.60,0:06:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德·塔斯克這樣的人涉足外交事務\NWhen a man like Raymond Tusk gets involved in state diplomacy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.36,0:06:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,絕不是為了獲得諾貝爾和平獎\Nyou can be sure he's not after the Nobel Peace Prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.97,0:06:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是個機會主義者  但我也是\NHe's an opportunist. But so am I.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也許這是我的機會  能讓他放鬆對總統的控制\NMaybe this is my opportunity to loosen his grip on the President.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.89,0:06:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副總統先生  你什麼時候回華盛頓\NMr. Vice President, when are you returning to Washington?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.39,0:06:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-副總統先生  你是否...  -副總統先生\N- Mr. Vice President, are you... - Mr. Vice President,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.96,0:06:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你會在斯波特瑟爾韋尼亞待多久\Ndo you have any idea how long you'll be in Spotsylvania?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.56,0:06:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對於跟中國的談判有什麼看法嗎\NAny comments on the talks with the Chinese?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.57,0:06:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能否就即將到來的峰會談判發表一下看法\NCan we get a comment on the upcoming Summit talks?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.39,0:06:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副總統今天\NVice President will be working
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.15,0:06:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,將在自己的房間裏辦公\Nfrom his room for the remainder of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.30,0:06:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有消息再通知你們\NWe'll let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.80,0:06:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  你什麼時候回華盛頓\NSir, when are you returning to Washington?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.39,0:07:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馮先生  很高興見到你\NMr. Feng. It's a pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.73,0:07:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彼此彼此  副總統先生\NLikewise, Mr. Vice President.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.38,0:07:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喝咖啡還是喝茶\NCoffee? Tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.55,0:07:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人問過了  謝謝\NI've already been offered, but thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝你  密查姆\NThank you, Meechum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.03,0:07:24.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,從北京飛過來時間很長\NIt's a long flight from Beijing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.67,0:07:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你一定累壞了\NYou must be exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.38,0:07:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直按西方時間作息\NI keep Western hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.05,0:07:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和你們沒有時差\NMy midnight is your midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.82,0:07:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你已經看過計劃書了嗎\NSo, have you had a chance to look over the proposal?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.95,0:07:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看了\NI have.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.92,0:07:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們開始吧\NShall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.22,0:07:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第四頁\NPage four.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.36,0:07:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,精煉廠\NThe refinery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.00,0:07:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,與塔斯克先生合作\NWith Mr. Tusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.95,0:07:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,與競標價最高的人合作\NWith the highest bidder.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.27,0:07:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們準備與克雷頓-維斯特簽訂一份\NWe're prepared to offer Clayton West
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.93,0:07:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,梅梅稀土金屬精煉廠的40年租約\Na 40-year lease on the Mei Mei Rare Earth Elements Refinery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.65,0:07:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,租約上會有我的名字\NTo which I will lend my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.90,0:07:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你和雷蒙德是生意夥伴\NI understand that you and Raymond are business associates,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.47,0:07:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你還是得公開招標\Nbut you're gonna have to open it up to bidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.85,0:08:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塔斯克先生出價肯定比其他人高\NMr. Tusk will outbid any competitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.93,0:08:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,儘管如此  過場還是得走\NWell, even so, you know, for appearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.60,0:08:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  過場  如果你堅持\NYes. Appearances. If you must.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.46,0:08:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那這裏就沒問題了\NSo, there are no issues here, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.67,0:08:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們繼續吧\NWe may proceed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.27,0:08:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第六頁\NPage six.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大橋\NThe bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,財政部外資投資管理委員會將批准\NThe Committee on Foreign Investment will approve
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.23,0:08:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一項基礎建設示範工程\Na pilot infrastructure project
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.12,0:08:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,建設一座從傑斐遜港到米爾福德市\Nto build a bridge over the Long Island Sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.57,0:08:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,橫跨長島海峽的大橋\Nfrom Port Jefferson to Milford,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.45,0:08:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以25年的過橋收費權作為交換\Nin exchange for a 25-year toll-taking contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.43,0:08:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我們考慮大橋前\NBefore we consider the bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.94,0:08:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想先討論另一件事\Nthere's one more item I'd like to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.19,0:08:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"考慮"  我以為大橋的事已經定了\N"Consider"? I thought the bridge was definite.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.35,0:08:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒什麼是確定的\NNothing is definite.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.55,0:08:40.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這座大橋是首要任務\NThis bridge is a priority-one item.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.63,0:08:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對你們總統非常重要  我明白\NIt's very important to your President. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.07,0:08:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想討論什麼\NWhat would you like to discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.20,0:08:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們在世界貿易組織\NThe currency manipulation suit which
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.58,0:08:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,指控我們進行匯率操縱\Nyou have filed against us in the World Trade Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.12,0:08:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們已經同意\NWhich we are prepared to drop
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.35,0:08:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果滿足其他條件就撤銷指控\Nif all other conditions are met.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.73,0:08:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們這次會面就是為了討論\NThe point of this meeting is to allow us
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.27,0:09:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不適合在正式場合談論的事  對嗎\Nto say things that cannot be said in formal settings, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.21,0:09:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  當然\NYes. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.22,0:09:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不希望你們撤訴\NWe don't want you to drop the lawsuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.00,0:09:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  我\NForgive me. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.91,0:09:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不明白\NI don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.01,0:09:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別在世貿組織讓步\NDo not back off in the WTO.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.89,0:09:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你們在匯率操縱上\NBut you've been fighting us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.31,0:09:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已經和我們鬥爭多年了\Non currency manipulation for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.04,0:09:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自由浮動匯率是大勢所趨\NA free-floating currency is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.15,0:09:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這下我有下手的空間了\NNow I have something I can work with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.66,0:09:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為什麼突然改變主意\NWhy the sudden change of heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.43,0:09:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,並不突然  只是我們這些有遠見的人\NNot sudden, it has taken those of us who are more forward-thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.19,0:09:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,花了很多年才說服其他同僚\Nmany years to convince our counterparts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.99,0:09:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那中國直接執行就得了\NBut China could just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.28,0:09:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你我都清楚  你們不需要世貿組織的裁定\NI mean, you know as well as I, you don't require a WTO ruling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.60,0:09:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像你說的  得走過場\NAppearances, as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.54,0:09:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一定要看起來像是受美國逼迫\NIt's important that it looks like America forced us out,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.82,0:09:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是我們主動投降\Nnot that we gave in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.70,0:09:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我需要時間\NWell, I'll need a little more time,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.24,0:09:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去和總統商量\Nso that I can brief the President.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.18,0:09:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我會耐心等待\NI'm here for as long as necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.78,0:09:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,無論你要找誰商量\NHowever you would like to communicate,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.38,0:09:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我都不管\NI leave that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.14,0:09:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝  副總統先生\NThank you, Mr. Vice President.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.40,0:09:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝  馮先生\NThank you, Mr. Feng.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.36,0:10:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在加夫尼我們有自己的外交特色\NIn Gaffney we had our own brand of diplomacy:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.22,0:10:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一邊握手言歡  一邊做好準備\NShake with your right hand, but hold a rock in your left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.01,0:10:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看是誰困在這兒了\NWell, look who got stuck with the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.62,0:10:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們來這兒簡直是找虐\NWe volunteered because we hate ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.13,0:10:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,南方前線一切順利吧\NAll's well on the Southern front?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.60,0:10:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒新聞就是沒新聞\NNo news is no news.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.62,0:10:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我聽說那裏還有火槍呢\NCome on. I hear there's muskets out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.96,0:10:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你什麼時候能給我們點猛料\NWhen you giving us something real?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.63,0:10:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們正身處美麗的斯波特瑟爾韋尼亞\NWe're here in beautiful Spotsylvania, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.52,0:10:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不過是給成年人玩玩具槍找借口\NThis is dress-up for grown men with toy guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.95,0:10:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聽起來可以寫上五百字\NSounds like 500 words to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.97,0:10:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告訴杜蘭特除非我們在世貿撤訴\NTell Durant that China won't discuss the bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.27,0:10:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否則中國不願意談大橋\Nunless we drop the WTO suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.13,0:10:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是說他們不希望撤訴嗎\NI thought you said they want to keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.86,0:10:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馮希望  說明塔斯克希望\NFeng does, which means Tusk does.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.44,0:10:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們不知道北京是不是希望\NBut we don't know if Beijing does.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.50,0:10:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得馮在撒謊\NYou think Feng's lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.08,0:10:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,開放匯率會導致利率市場化\NAn open currency could free up interest rates,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.67,0:10:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,減小中國的通貨膨脹\Nreduce inflation in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.92,0:10:47.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們兩人都能受益\NThey'd both profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.92,0:10:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他們或者我們將了北京的軍\NIf they're forcing Beijing's hand, or we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.66,0:10:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能在峰會引起混亂\Nthat could throw the Summit into chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.08,0:10:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正是  馮可能有後台支持\NExactly. Look, Feng may well have support,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.43,0:10:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我猜常委會有分歧\Nbut my guess is that the Standing Committee's divided.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.57,0:10:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎樣  我們打他們個措手不及\NEither way, we'll throw 'em off balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.43,0:11:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凱茜一宣佈  我們就放出撤訴的風聲\NLet's leak we're dropping the suit as soon as Cathy presents it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.89,0:11:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是訴訟嗎  不漏點別的什麼\NJust the lawsuit? Nothing else in the leak?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.27,0:11:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,暗示與馮有關  但別點名\NA hint of Feng, but no names.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.67,0:11:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓消息傳一陣子再說\NLet's let this grow on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.38,0:11:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這回怎樣\NHow was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.40,0:11:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好多了\NMuch better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.99,0:11:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我感覺不錯  你怎麼看\NI feel good. What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.73,0:11:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看你準備好了\NI think you're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.08,0:11:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,代碼還得準備多久\NHow long on the code?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.34,0:11:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只差幾個漏洞了\NJust a couple of bugs to work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.43,0:11:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我說明天或週三我就能回去\NI told them tomorrow or Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.83,0:11:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,活兒還沒完\NWork's not done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.95,0:11:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要是再往後推  你不覺得別人會奇怪嗎\NIf I postpone again, don't you think it'll draw attention? I --
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.05,0:11:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等完事了也就沒事了\NIt'll be done when it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.18,0:11:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,漏洞修復了我就給你發郵件\NI'll email you when the bugs are fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.86,0:11:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,挑一個公開的場所  約好時間給你\NSomewhere public, a place and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.43,0:11:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你真想這麼做嗎\NHey, are you sure you wanna do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.71,0:11:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我明白風險多大\NI understand the risks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.62,0:11:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你自以為明白而已\NWell, you think you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.50,0:11:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不是頭回身陷險境了\NThis isn't the first time I've been in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.40,0:11:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是嗎  在《先驅報》被紙割傷過手嗎\NOh, yeah? Paper cuts at The Herald?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.79,0:11:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,死亡威脅  我揭露了一個特區販毒集團\NDeath threats. When I exposed a drug ring in D.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.59,0:11:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我讀過你寫的報道\NYou know, I read the articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.84,0:11:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那根本不算什麼\NThat's small time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.18,0:11:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我差點就接受司法保護了\NI almost had to go into protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.93,0:12:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這可是聯調局  不是什麼街警\NThis is the FBI. It's not a few street cops.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.80,0:12:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得自己反抗當局\NYou think you're badass because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.96,0:12:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是個了不得的義士嗎\Nyou're on some vigilante anarchy kick?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.96,0:12:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,起碼我有膽子在報道上署上真實姓名\NAt least I have the balls to put my name on the work I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.17,0:12:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你沒面臨過幾百年的刑罰\NYou've never faced a hundred years in prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.68,0:12:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你這自以為是的混蛋\Nyou self-righteous prick.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.81,0:12:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我大多數朋友被關起來  永遠出不來\NMost of my friends are locked up and rotting away
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.71,0:12:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就因為他們太多次以身犯險\N'cause they poked the bear one too many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.48,0:12:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為什麼  因為他們想揭露政府的監控項目\NWhy? They wanted to expose government surveillance,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.62,0:12:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,棱鏡計劃  挪用公款  濫用職權  酷刑和欺騙\Nthe PRISM program, embezzlement, abuse, fucking torture, lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.65,0:12:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是個記者有什麼了不起  我們是戰士\NYou're a journalist. Who gives a shit? We're fucking soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.33,0:12:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這已經是我生活的一部分了\NIt's personal for me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.58,0:12:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我沒選擇了  但你還有\NI don't have a choice, but you still do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.85,0:12:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也沒選擇了\NI don't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.13,0:12:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,消息從哪來\NWhere did you get this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.38,0:12:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以說消息源與中國代表團關係密切\NYou could say a source close to the Chinese delegation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.85,0:12:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給我個名字\NGive me a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.62,0:12:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只知道是一個中國商人\NAll I know is that it's a Chinese businessman
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.30,0:13:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和常委會關係非同一般  在峰會上進行秘密外交\Nwith ties to the Standing Committee back-channeling the Summit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.04,0:13:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他人在華盛頓嗎  -我不知道\N- In Washington? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.29,0:13:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-在和誰接觸  -這我也不知道\N- With who? - I don't know that either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.11,0:13:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我去問貿易代表處  他們會證實嗎\NIf I call the USTR's office, they'll confirm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.66,0:13:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道多少  就告訴了你多少\NI'm telling you as much as I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.09,0:13:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你為什麼要告訴我\NWhy are you telling me this at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.95,0:13:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反正明天他們也會把消息放出去\NThey're going public with it tomorrow anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.28,0:13:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不如讓你搶先發佈\NYou might as well get the scoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.52,0:13:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為什麼挑中我\NWhy me, specifically?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.66,0:13:17.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,內戰重演的報道配不上你這樣的記者\NYou deserve better than a Civil War reenactment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.90,0:13:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別裝做你突然變成聖誕老人了\NPlease don't pretend you've suddenly become Santa Claus.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.52,0:13:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我現在幫你的忙  也許你會承我的情\NI give you something now, maybe you'll remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.94,0:13:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,將來有一天或許用得上\NIt's an investment in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.03,0:13:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可不太喜歡賣人情\NI'm not big on favors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.27,0:13:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我說了"也許"\NI just said "maybe."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.98,0:13:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馬上給我接貿易代表處\NConnect me to the USTR's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.50,0:13:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,越過新聞發言人\NSkip the Press Secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.39,0:13:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟他們說我想問世貿組織訴訟的事\NTell them I want to talk about the WTO suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.49,0:13:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你跟誰說了\NWho did you speak to?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.79,0:13:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,康納  他在向艾拉·薩伊德洩露消息\NConnor. He's talking to Ayla Sayyad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.58,0:13:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你透給他多少\NHow much did you fill him in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.46,0:13:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒說多少\NThe bare minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.59,0:13:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要是按之前說好的\NI'd be a lot more comfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.76,0:13:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你親自去說  我會放心許多\Nif it was you going directly, as we discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.15,0:13:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這樣就牽涉不到我  你也就更安全了\NThis puts distance on me, which puts distance on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.16,0:13:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你今晚親自去見馮\NI want you to meet with Feng tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.61,0:14:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不用中間人  -明白\N- No proxies. - Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.84,0:14:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,古德溫先生那邊辦得如何了\NNow where are we with Mr. Goodwin?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.72,0:14:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,隨時可以下手  判個35年或者無期\NAny day now. Thirty-five to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.58,0:14:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,網絡恐怖主義  判刑都很重\NCyber terrorism. Penalties are stiff.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.62,0:14:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,務必做得乾淨利落  道格\NThis needs to be clean, Doug.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.17,0:14:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,會的\NIt will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.10,0:14:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一擊致命\NOne fall of the axe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.32,0:14:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有消息告訴我\NKeep me informed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.46,0:14:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  先生\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.92,0:14:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我認為你的做法真是太勇敢了\NWell, I just think what you did took so much bravery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.16,0:14:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在直播節目上  當著全國觀眾的面\NTo go on air like that, in front of the whole country,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.50,0:14:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,講出你的經歷\Nand say what you did?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.19,0:14:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這對我的確不容易\NThat means a lot to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.98,0:14:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很欽佩兩位的努力  為了幫助\NAnd I admire what you both have been doing to advocate for the –
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.54,0:14:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些受害者\Nwell, for the victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.45,0:14:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是女性  就像你和我  不只是受害者\NWell, women, like you and me. Not victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.56,0:14:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還有男人  這無關性別\NMen, too. It's not gender-specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.92,0:14:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\NWell, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.76,0:14:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你願意參與進來嗎\NWould you consider pitching in?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.42,0:14:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼參與\NHow?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.38,0:14:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果有第一夫人支持  我們的表態就有力多了\NIt would send a strong message if we had the First Lady in our corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.16,0:15:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你覺得我能幫上忙的話\NIf you think I could help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.90,0:15:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,婦女黨團的領袖\NWell, if the head of the Women's Caucus,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.43,0:15:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及白宮的第一和第二夫人加起來...\Nboth wives from the White House...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.78,0:15:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這樣的組合他們沒法無視\NThat's a meeting they couldn't sweep under the rug.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.33,0:15:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席肯派人來  就已經是很好的兆頭了\NAnd the fact that the Chairman sent anyone is promising,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.88,0:15:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們得保證他真能聽到我們的聲音\Nbut we need to make sure our message gets back to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.28,0:15:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是  我沒有過此類經歷\NI just...I haven't been through the same sort of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.50,0:15:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這有什麼妨礙呢\NWell, why should that prevent you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.06,0:15:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道我是不是有發言權\NI don't know if I have a right to speak about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可是第一夫人\NYou're the First Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.15,0:15:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有權發表任何言論\NYou have a right to speak about anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.55,0:15:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-懷特先生  -馬博利太太\N- Mr. White? - Mrs. Marbury.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.47,0:15:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叫我蘇珊\NI'm Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.58,0:15:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很高興見到你\NWell, it's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.83,0:15:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道這裏挺偏僻的\NI know I'm a little off the beaten path.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.00,0:15:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找這裏困難嗎\NDid you have any trouble finding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.04,0:15:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  您給的指示很明確  找起來很輕鬆\NNo. The directions were great. Easy as pie.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.32,0:15:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就好\NWell, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請進\NCome in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.24,0:15:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得承認  我都期待一整天了\NI have to admit I've been looking forward to this all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.44,0:15:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒想到你們這麼快就要宣佈了\NI didn't realize you were announcing so soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.55,0:15:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們收到了慷慨的捐款\NWe've had some great luck with the endowment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.19,0:15:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我丈夫生前沒受到多少嘉獎\NWell, my husband didn't get much recognition while he was alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.98,0:16:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,計劃生育協會想以他來命名基金\NI was so thrilled when Planned Parenthood asked to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.64,0:16:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真讓我激動\Nname a fund after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.46,0:16:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您肯同意  我們也很高興\NWell, we're thrilled that you're open to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.20,0:16:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你之前打電話說有些問題要問\NWhen you called, you said you had some questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.05,0:16:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,問題挺敏感的  所以我想親自來問\NThey're delicate. That's why I wanted to come in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.04,0:16:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼個"敏感"法\N"Delicate", how?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.86,0:16:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多人會抗議向未成年人\NThere are a lot of people who will protest
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.69,0:16:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提供這方面的經濟資助\Nthis sort of financial assistance to minors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.94,0:16:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們得保證他們找不到誹謗我們的根據\NAnd we want to make sure they have no cause to smear us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.96,0:16:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我丈夫這輩子  總有人想詆毀他\NPeople tried to smear my husband his entire career.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.79,0:16:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他從不讓這些事影響他的工作\NHe never let it affect the work he was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.40,0:16:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您丈夫實施過任何非法墮胎手術嗎\NDid your husband ever perform any illegal abortions?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.09,0:16:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我需要您的答案  馬博利太太\NI need you to answer me, Mrs. Marbury.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.06,0:16:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您丈夫實施過任何非法墮胎手術嗎\NDid your husband perform any illegal abortions?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.61,0:16:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想討論這個\NI won't discuss that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.63,0:16:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有未上報的嗎\NNothing unreported?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.10,0:16:47.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,年輕人  你年紀不大  不會記得\NYoung man, you're not old enough to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.54,0:16:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但在過去  人人...\NBut there was a time when everybody --
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.52,0:16:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有沒有涉及什麼大人物\NWhat about any prominent figures
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.87,0:16:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能被反墮胎人士拿來當靶子的\Nwho the Anti-Choice crowd could vilify?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.96,0:16:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.20,0:16:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馬博利醫生有沒有為克萊爾·安德伍德做過墮胎\NDid Dr. Marbury perform an abortion for Claire Underwood?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.76,0:17:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  他沒有\NNo, he did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.70,0:17:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道他做過\NI know for a fact that he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.80,0:17:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是謊話  我想請你馬上離開\NThat is not true, and I would like you to leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.60,0:17:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  馬博利太太\NForgive me, Mrs. Marbury.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.41,0:17:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我對您沒說實話\NI haven't been entirely honest with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.41,0:17:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我叫賽斯·格雷森\NMy name's Seth Grayson.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.42,0:17:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不為計劃生育協會工作\NI don't work for Planned Parenthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.72,0:17:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馮先生
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.93,0:17:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,國內常委們推測  搞秘密外交的是你
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.68,0:17:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}華爾街電訊報
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.68,0:17:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}美國在世貿組織撤訴
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.45,0:17:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,香港出現了兩篇文章
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.54,0:17:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都提到了你的名字
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.10,0:17:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要我聯繫副總統嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.64,0:17:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  讓他來找我\NNo. Let him come to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.18,0:17:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給塔斯克先生打電話\NGet Mr. Tusk on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.80,0:17:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你真該為自己感到羞愧\NYou should ashamed of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.84,0:17:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是為了你好  馬博利太太\NI'm doing this for your own good, Mrs. Marbury.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.86,0:17:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想想媒體炒作的後果\NImagine the media frenzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.99,0:17:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您丈夫生前的名聲盡毀\NYour husband's legacy, destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.46,0:17:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,媒體日日夜夜追著您不放\NThe press hounding you, day and night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.75,0:18:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,計劃生育基金  也沒有了\NAnd Planned Parenthood Fund, gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.24,0:18:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怎麼知道你是不是為她工作\NHow do I know you work for her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.30,0:18:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是什麼右翼狂熱分子  打算摧毀...\NThat you're not just some right-wing fanatic who wants to destro?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.75,0:18:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否則我就不會親自登門拜訪了\NBecause I wouldn't have done you the courtesy of paying a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.79,0:18:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,來的就不是我\NThere would've been an army of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.95,0:18:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是一隊衛星轉播車了\Nsatellite trucks at your door instead of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.44,0:18:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不會告訴任何人的  如果你是擔心這個\NWell, I won't tell anyone, if that's what you're worried about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.57,0:18:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信您\NI believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.50,0:18:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您丈夫有沒有對他幫助過的女人做過任何記錄\NDid your husband keep records of any kind of who he assisted?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.16,0:18:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,任何東西  筆記或非公開記錄\NAnything at all? Notes? Unofficial records?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.42,0:18:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有一本日記\NHe kept a journal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.21,0:18:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您還能找到嗎\NDo you still have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.23,0:18:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能看看嗎\NMay I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.12,0:18:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看吧\NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.07,0:18:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得把它帶走\NOh. I need to take this with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.11,0:19:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能把那頁撕掉嗎\NCan't you just take out that page?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.69,0:19:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果有人找到這本日記  這幾頁又缺了\NSomeone finds this with pages missing,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.41,0:19:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那會引起懷疑\Nthat could raise eyebrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.14,0:19:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這裏面有他60年的人生\NThere's 60 years of his life in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.27,0:19:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,從我們相遇到他去世\NFrom when we met until he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.83,0:19:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那您希望那六十年被遺忘\NAnd do you want six decades
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卻只剩下25年前8月的一個晚上嗎\Nreduced to one night in August...25 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.56,0:19:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想像一下這裏當時的情形\NNow just imagine what it looked like back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.85,0:19:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,山脊邊緣是茂密的灌木叢\NThe edge of the ridge was a dense thicket,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.49,0:19:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北方軍隊得以長驅直入  在騾子鞋列隊\Nwhich allowed the Northern troops to come in and form on the Mule Shoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.61,0:19:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,南方軍在山脊頂端\NNow the Southern regiments were entrenched
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.51,0:19:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這一帶挖好了戰壕\Nin this area at the apex of the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.97,0:19:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如您所見\NAs you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.80,0:19:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這裏的地形迫使雙方向下走  逼近彼此\Nthe topography really forced the two sides down towards each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.49,0:19:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這裏就是血腥角\NThis is the Bloody Angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.14,0:19:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒錯\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.15,0:19:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我昨晚還讀到了相關內容\NI was reading about it last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.70,0:19:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,短兵相接  白刃相見\NClose quarters, hand-to-hand combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.14,0:19:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,據說  南北雙方共有一萬五千名士兵\NAll told, about 15,000 Union-Confederate soldiers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.64,0:19:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在血腥角這塊半英里寬的戰場上\Nlost their lives here at the Bloody Angle, on a battlefield
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.65,0:19:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,失去了生命\Nthat's only about half a mile wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.88,0:19:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副總統先生  我們今天為您準備了一份驚喜\NNow, Mr. Vice President, we have a surprise for you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.67,0:20:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向您介紹麥高文旅第12軍團的\NI'd like to introduce you to Corporal Augustus Elijah Underwood
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.07,0:20:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奧古斯都·以利亞·安德伍德下士\Nof the 12th Regiment of the McGowan Brigade,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.77,0:20:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您的曾曾曾祖父\Nyour great-great-great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.30,0:20:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在這場戰役中犧牲於此\NI died here in this battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.27,0:20:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我覺得是搞錯了吧\NI think there's been a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.01,0:20:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我祖父從沒說過祖上有人參加過內戰\NMy grandfather never mentioned any Underwoods in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.62,0:20:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們做過調查\NWe did our research.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.34,0:20:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他就是在這裏戰鬥犧牲的\NHe definitely fought and died here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.91,0:20:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只有24歲  而我兒子\NI was 24. And my son,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.21,0:20:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的曾曾祖父只有兩歲\Nyour great-great-grandfather was two years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.91,0:20:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我從沒見過他\NI never met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.07,0:20:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是在這裏嗎  在血腥角\NIt happened here, at the Bloody Angle?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.62,0:20:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在那片林子邊上\NAt the edge of those woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.69,0:20:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的腦袋被石頭砸扁了\NMy skull was bashed in with a rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.34,0:20:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奧古斯都  謝謝你\NAugustus, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.45,0:20:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這邊  還有一些\NNow, uh, over here we've got something that's,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.96,0:20:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有趣的東西\Nuh, very interesting as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.31,0:20:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等一下\NUh, j—just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.69,0:20:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接著說\NTell me more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.04,0:20:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,當時正是半夜\NIt was the middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.35,0:20:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們的子彈打光了  只剩下刺刀\NAnd we were out of musket balls, just bayonets.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.91,0:20:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且只有一半人有刺刀  我什麼都沒有\NOnly half of us had those. I had nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.05,0:20:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只能靠這雙手\NJust these hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.59,0:20:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天很黑  什麼都看不見\NSo dark, couldn't see nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.56,0:20:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但能聽北方佬在朝我們跑來\NBut you could hear 'em, the Yanks, runnin' toward us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.29,0:20:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接著就能聞到他們了\NAnd then you could smell 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.27,0:21:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我遇到的第一個北方佬\NFirst Yank that brushed up against me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.61,0:21:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被我掐住了脖子  倒在地上\NI grab him by the throat, fall down on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.32,0:21:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我用力打他  打到皮開肉綻\NI bit him so hard, I could taste the bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.86,0:21:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然後他抓起一塊石頭  砸中了這裏\NThen he grabs a rock and brings it down right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.13,0:21:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就這麼死了\NAnd that was that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.79,0:21:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我被埋在萬人冢裏  沒有墓碑\NI was buried in a mass grave, no headstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.39,0:21:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能給您和奧古斯都拍張合影嗎\NCould we get a picture with you and Augustus?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.76,0:21:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.23,0:21:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝你\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.89,0:21:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他相當認真啊\NHe takes it rather seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.58,0:21:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊  他們都很認真\NOh, yeah. They all do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.84,0:21:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前面有我們重建的\NNow, up ahead, we have examples of,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.95,0:21:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,邦聯軍壁壘的模型\Nuh, Confederate ramparts that we've reconstructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.70,0:21:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以看到他們是如何伐木挖戰壕的\NAnd you can see how they cut the timber and made the trenches.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.11,0:21:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在戰鬥過程中\NNow these trenches traded hands
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.35,0:21:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這些戰壕幾次易手\Nmany times over the course of the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.27,0:21:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有鑰匙\NYou have keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.74,0:21:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你歸我們管  沒錯  我們有鑰匙\NWe own you. Yes, we have keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.88,0:21:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我去把衣服穿上\NI'm gonna put some clothes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.80,0:22:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別想衣服的事了\NForget your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.88,0:22:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的原話"你真想這麼做嗎"\NAnd I quote, "You sure you wanna do this?"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.36,0:22:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"我沒選擇了  但你還有"\NAnd I quote, "I don't have a choice, but you do."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.82,0:22:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你他媽以為自己在幹什麼\NWhat the fuck do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.68,0:22:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他應該知道他究竟要做什麼\NHe should know what he's getting into.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是絲綢睡褲嗎\NAre those silk pajamas?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.60,0:22:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,近距離看更有檔次了\NLooks even fancier in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.80,0:22:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,腰果\NCashew.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.55,0:22:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  別碰她\NNo. Don't touch her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.04,0:22:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,過來  小傢伙\NHey, there, little guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.18,0:22:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以前在監控裏見過你\NI've seen you before on camera, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.37,0:22:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請把她放下\NPlease put her down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.98,0:22:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要冒險\NDon't take the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.79,0:22:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這這雙鞋是在彭尼百貨公司買的\NI bought these shoes at J.C. Penney,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.88,0:22:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,含稅價72塊\N$72 with tax.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.35,0:22:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,橡膠鞋底  用水就能沖乾淨\NRubber soles. You can clean 'em off with a hose.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.25,0:22:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,求求你  你弄傷她了\NPlease, you're hurting her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.96,0:23:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也有一隻寵物  他叫嘉文·奧爾西\NI have a pet, too. His name is Gavin Orsay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.31,0:23:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐下\NSit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.41,0:23:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我說"坐下"\NI said, "Sit."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.57,0:23:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瞧瞧你多乖呀  嘉文\NLook what a good boy you are, Gavin.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.61,0:23:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想讓我這麼做嗎\NIs that what you need me to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.82,0:23:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安靜  我說"去撿"  你就去\NQuiet. When I say "fetch," you fetch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.66,0:23:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在我們去抓盧卡斯  就像我們說好的那樣\NAnd now we are going to fetch Lucas, just like we discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.98,0:23:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要是敢咬我  我就殺了你\NIf you try to bite my hand, I will put you to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.58,0:23:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,介意我拿兩瓶嗎\NMind if I take a couple?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.76,0:24:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,道格·斯坦普  我是副總統的幕僚長\NDoug Stamper, I'm the Vice President's Chief of Staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.27,0:24:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道  坐吧\NI know. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.44,0:24:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我祖父參加過革命\NMy grandfather fought in the Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.53,0:24:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中國當時很窮\NChina was poor, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.07,0:24:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很難買到糖\NSugar was hard to come by.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.39,0:24:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在中國到處能買到糖\NNow sugar's everywhere in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.65,0:24:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要來杯古典雞尾酒嗎\NDo you like Old-Fashioneds?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.57,0:24:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  謝謝\NNo, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.94,0:24:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看到新聞了\NI've seen the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.95,0:24:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們政府對我們撤訴非常高興\NYour government was enthusiastic about our dropping the suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.03,0:24:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們還在國內將其鼓吹為一場勝利\NThey've touted it as a victory back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.27,0:24:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,確實是勝利  但不是我們想要的勝利\NIt is a victory, but not the victory we wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.75,0:24:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這讓我們很難相信\NWe're finding that difficult to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.68,0:24:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你說我們  是指副總統吧\NBy "we," you mean the Vice President.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.70,0:24:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我指的是美國政府\NI mean the American government.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.18,0:24:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他聲稱自己就代表美國政府\NWhich he proclaims to represent.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.66,0:24:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒錯  而我代表他\NHe does. And I'm representing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.97,0:24:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斯坦普先生  別吹噓你的地位\NDon't inflate your status, Mr. Stamper.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.20,0:24:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不過是個跑腿的\NYou're nothing but an errand boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.77,0:25:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要對副總統說什麼嗎\NDo you have a message for the Vice President?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.08,0:25:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他代表美國政府\NIf he represents the American government,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.52,0:25:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那他為什麼沒能轉達我的要求\Nthen why did he fail to communicate my request?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.07,0:25:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們質疑你的合法性  馮先生\NWe question your legitimacy, Mr. Feng.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.28,0:25:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們代表團的做法和言論\NNothing your delegation has done or said has,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.20,0:25:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都與你的要求背道而馳\Nin any way, supported your requests.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.12,0:25:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聞聞\NSmell that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.96,0:25:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我用了高檔珍稀的麥卡倫\NI use Macallan Rare and Fine,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.34,0:25:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1926年產  一瓶四萬美金\N1926. $40,000 a bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.84,0:25:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以前酗酒  是嗎\NYou used to be an alcoholic, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.02,0:25:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,酒癮是戒不掉的  只能克制\NNot "used to be." Still am. A sober one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.10,0:25:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你懷念這味道嗎\NDo you miss it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.27,0:25:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那可是五千美元\NFive thousand dollars you just spilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.97,0:25:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我會寄張支票給你\NI'll send you a check.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.33,0:25:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜歡你  斯坦普先生  即便你只是個跑腿的\NI like you, Mr. Stamper, even if you're just an errand boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.40,0:25:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我再問你一次\NI'll ask you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.42,0:25:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要對副總統說什麼嗎\NWhat is your message for the Vice President?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.02,0:25:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恢復起訴  否則傑斐遜港大橋項目將取消\NThere will be no Port Jefferson Bridge unless the lawsuit is reintroduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.91,0:25:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到時  常委會會有人抗議\NWhen you do, there will be those on the Standing Committee who protest,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.28,0:25:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我會搞定他們\Nbut I'll manage them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.37,0:25:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大多數人想要改革\NThe majority want reform.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.16,0:26:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我會告訴副總統\NI'll tell the Vice President.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.84,0:26:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斯坦普先生  還有一條\NMr. Stamper, one more message.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.80,0:26:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請提醒副總統  我們來這裏\NPlease remind the Vice President that we are both here
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.92,0:26:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是應我們共同的朋友塔斯克先生的邀請\Nat the behest of our mutual friend, Mr. Tusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.59,0:26:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果副總統不願意合作  我就直接跳過他\NIf the Vice President fails to cooperate, I will simply bypass him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.10,0:26:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼了\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.52,0:26:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是道格\NIt's Doug.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.65,0:26:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.93,0:26:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟馮談了\NSpoke with Feng.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.96,0:26:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給你的洋蔥圈\NHere's your onion rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.60,0:26:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道朗斯特裏特將軍就是在這裏\NDid you know that General Longstreet was shot here,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.96,0:26:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被他自己人意外誤傷害死的\Naccidentally, by his own men in the dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.27,0:26:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  我不知道\NNo...I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.54,0:26:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  跟我介紹一下進展吧\NAll right. Bring me up to date.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.30,0:26:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟馮談得怎麼樣了\NWhere are we with Feng?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.29,0:26:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要我們恢復訴訟\NHe wants us to resume the lawsuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.67,0:26:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看來他要堅持立場\NSo, he's sticking to his guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.63,0:26:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不起訴  大橋項目就取消\NIf we don't reintroduce it, there's no bridge project.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.24,0:27:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那樣總統會很失望\NWell, that would greatly upset the President.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.47,0:27:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要我轉達馮的意思嗎\NDo you want me to deliver Feng's message?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.40,0:27:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,絕對不要\NAbsolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.00,0:27:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們就要讓總統生氣\NWe want the President angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.09,0:27:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不過要想辦法不讓他怪罪在我身上\NThe tricky part is making sure he doesn't direct it toward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.67,0:27:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你要我做什麼\NSo what do you want me to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.57,0:27:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聯繫凱茜的人\NGet a hold of Cathy's people.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.73,0:27:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,決不能提及訴訟\NDo not mention the lawsuit at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.24,0:27:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓他們自己提大橋項目\NHave them bring up the bridge instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.63,0:27:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看馮是不是在虛張聲勢\NLet's see if Feng is bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.70,0:27:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  先生\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.82,0:27:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得吸取朗斯特裏特的教訓  他樹大招風\NWe must learn from Longstreet. He rode too high in the saddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.54,0:27:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果明天有人朝我開槍\NIf a bullet comes my way tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.12,0:27:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那絕不會是意外  而且我得趕快躲開\Nit will not be an accident, and I must be quick to duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.65,0:27:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生們  感謝你們的到來\NGentlemen, thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.74,0:27:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副總統會出席嗎\NIs the Vice President attending?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.73,0:27:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不會  他不在華盛頓\NNo, he's not. He's out of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.54,0:27:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是決定用他的辦公室\NI just decided to use his office
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.51,0:27:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為他的比我的大得多\Nbecause it's a bit bigger than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.45,0:27:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請坐吧\NPlease, sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.81,0:27:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道這不是你們第一次\NI know this isn't the first conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.57,0:28:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,談性侵犯的問題\Nyou've had about sexual assault.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.12,0:28:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們和議員女士\NWe've had a very open dialogue
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.48,0:28:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已經進行了一段時間的公開對話了\Nwith the Congresswoman for quite some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.56,0:28:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以說"公開"\N"Open" is one way to put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.65,0:28:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我倒覺得參謀長聯席會議只是在默默忍受我\NI think the Joint Chiefs have tolerated my concerns, but
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.14,0:28:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,公平來講  我們一直有做出積極回應\NTo be fair, we've been quite responsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.14,0:28:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,過去兩年裏...\NOver the past two years alone, we --
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.01,0:28:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,議員女士對我表達了她的沮喪\NThe Congresswoman has expressed her frustration to me
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.33,0:28:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為這件事上仍有改進空間\Nthat there's still room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.70,0:28:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安德伍德夫人  我能說幾句嗎\NMrs. Underwood, if I may.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.06,0:28:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請講\NPlease.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.88,0:28:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這件事我們十分看重\NThis is an issue we've grappled with seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.60,0:28:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們增加了相關教育和防範措施\NIncreased education and prevention measures,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.93,0:28:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,整改匯報流程\Nrestructuring the reporting process,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.14,0:28:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杜絕軍事法庭的濫用職權現象\Ninsulating courts martial from abuse of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.71,0:28:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但還是不夠\NIt's still not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.09,0:28:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不會進行民事審判的\NCivilian jurisdiction is not gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.61,0:28:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們都清楚這是議員女士所希望的\NWe're all aware that's what the Congresswoman would prefer,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.29,0:28:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我們不會允許我們...\Nbut we won't allow our cha--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.99,0:28:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我遲到了嗎\NAm I late?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.61,0:28:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我的錯  會面提前了\NIt's my fault. The meeting got pushed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.40,0:28:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我本想給你發郵件的  非常抱歉\NI meant to email you. I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.28,0:28:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒關係  請坐\NThat's fine. Please, sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.26,0:28:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不知道您也會來  沃剋夫人\NWe didn't know you'd be attending, Mrs. Walker.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.77,0:28:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉打斷你們了\NI'm sorry for interrupting.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.85,0:28:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請繼續\NContinue.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.62,0:28:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正如我剛剛所說\NAs I was saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.22,0:29:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,將性侵案件的審判權完全交給民事法庭\Nputting sexual assault cases entirely in the hands of civilian courts
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.73,0:29:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,從根本上侵蝕了軍隊自我約束的能力\Nfundamentally erodes the military's ability to self-discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.10,0:29:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那要是實施民事監管  而不是民事法庭呢\NWhat about civilian oversight instead of civilian courts?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.45,0:29:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,任何讓步  都會一發不可收拾\NThat's a slippery slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.97,0:29:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對於種族融合  也曾有人說過類似的話\NThere were those who said the same about racial integration.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.25,0:29:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,融合沒有改變核心的運作本質...\NIntegration didn't change the core operational nature of the --
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.06,0:29:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但的確證明了軍方可以實現自我改革\NBut it did prove that the military could shape its own evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.25,0:29:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是沒錯  但就這個問題\NAbsolutely. But in this case,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.67,0:29:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,民事監管不是解決辦法\Ncivilian oversight is not the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.94,0:29:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我丈夫沒有軍銜  但他監管軍方\NMy husband is a civilian who oversees the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.96,0:29:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你難道想說\NAre you suggesting that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.15,0:29:33.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,民眾在這種問題上無從提供指導嗎\Ncivilians can offer no guidance in matters like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.05,0:29:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  沃剋夫人  我完全不是那個意思\NForgive me, Mrs. Walker. I didn't mean to suggest that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.60,0:29:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那或許你該聽聽你對面的民眾是怎麼想的\NThen maybe you should listen to the civilian sitting across from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.12,0:29:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,當然  夫人\NYes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.32,0:29:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是你們出版的性侵防範讀物\NThis is from your own sexual assault prevention literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.24,0:29:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上面寫道  有些情況下\NAnd in it, it says in some cases
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.73,0:29:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更應該屈從  而不是抵抗\Nit may be advisable to submit than to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.54,0:30:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我想  這方面顯然還有可以改進的地方\NI think it's quite clear that there's still room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.93,0:30:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道馮山德嗎\NDid you know about Xander Feng?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.46,0:30:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在新聞上看到才知道的\NNot 'til I saw his name on the wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.46,0:30:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}美聯社  路透社等大新聞通訊社發佈的新聞  媒體獲得後會進行轉載
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.19,0:30:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他曾兩次被指控腐敗\NHe's been charged with corruption twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.94,0:30:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,兩次指控都撤銷了\NBoth times the charges were dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.33,0:30:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道在中國獲罪後會怎樣嗎\NDo you know what happens in China if you're convicted?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.17,0:30:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我猜不會有好事  -判死刑\N- I'm guessing it's not good. - You die.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.50,0:30:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我說對了\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.23,0:30:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這人如果再上"過場法庭"\NWe're talking about a man who's only one kangaroo court
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.23,0:30:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}指完全是擺擺樣子的法庭  根本不會認真按照法律進行審判
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.23,0:30:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就必死無疑\Naway from lethal injection,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.91,0:30:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且他富可敵國  腐敗昭然若揭\Nwho's filthy rich and clearly corrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.83,0:30:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中方就派這樣的人來嗎\NAnd this is who the Chinese send?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.56,0:30:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你問錯人了\NYou're asking the wrong guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.09,0:30:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別再躲躲閃閃了\NStop dodging.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.16,0:30:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不過是傳了個話  僅此而已\NI passed a note in class. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.44,0:30:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們信任你  弗蘭克\NWe placed our faith in you, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.55,0:30:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們還有今明兩天時間  總統先生\NWe still have the rest of the day and all of tomorrow, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.91,0:30:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我需要這座橋\NI need this bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.89,0:30:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否則我的基建項目就得叫停\NOtherwise, we have to stall my infrastructure program.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.25,0:30:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有外國投資  沒法削減赤字\NNo foreign investment, no deficit reduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.66,0:30:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中方知道這一點\NAnd the Chinese know this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.65,0:30:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們就是拿這個做籌碼\NThey're using it for leverage.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.78,0:30:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是為了什麼呢\NYeah, but for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.77,0:30:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不清楚\NWell, that I'm not sure of.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.28,0:30:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我們派你去斯波特瑟爾韋尼亞幹什麼  弗蘭克\NThen why did we send you to Spotsylvania, Frank?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.13,0:30:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這些問題你該心裏有數的\NYou're supposed to have answers to these questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.09,0:31:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生  我一小時前和馮先生聯繫過\NMr. President, I spoke to Mr. Feng an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.30,0:31:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他怎麼說\NWhat'd he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.85,0:31:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,子彈來了\NHere comes the bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.71,0:31:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他說弗蘭克沒表達清楚他的意思\NHe claims that Frank hasn't been delivering his messages properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.68,0:31:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已經逐字複述了他的要求\NI have conveyed his requests word for word.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.43,0:31:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他說  你一直在唱反調\NHe says you've been doing the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.39,0:31:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,究竟是誰在負責私下溝通  我還是雷蒙德\NWhose responsible for the back-channeling here, me or Raymond?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.71,0:31:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你  弗蘭克\NYou are, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.85,0:31:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是來幫忙的  不是來談判的\NI'm simply here to facilitate, not negotiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.34,0:31:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可你還繼續私下聯繫\NAnd yet you continue to have private conversations with
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.44,0:31:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北京所謂的密使\NBeijing's supposed emissary.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.32,0:31:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,聽著  弗蘭克\NListen, Frank --
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.20,0:31:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要信任馮先生  而不是我嗎  雷蒙德\NAre you prepared to trust Mr. Feng's word over mine, Raymond?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.17,0:31:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒人質疑你的話  弗蘭克\NNo one is doubting your word, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.78,0:31:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果馮真的是為了他政府的利益\NWell, if Feng is truly representing his government's interest,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.26,0:31:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為什麼他在我這兒一套  雷蒙德那兒一套\Nthen why is he telling Raymond one thing and telling me another?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.88,0:31:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那大橋項目取消是怎麼回事\NHow do you explain the bridge falling through?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.93,0:31:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自由浮動匯率能讓他受益\NWell, he personally profits from a free-floating currency,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.98,0:31:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和他合作的人都是如此\Njust as anyone would who's in business with him,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.30,0:31:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就比如你  雷蒙德\Nsuch as yourself, Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.76,0:31:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,精煉廠和大橋是兩碼事\NThe refinery and the bridge are two completely different issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.64,0:31:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們先說橋的事\NLet's keep our focus, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.30,0:31:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必須重談建橋的事  沒得商量\NI want the bridge back on the table, end of story.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.91,0:31:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-凱瑟琳  -我明早第一個提這件事\N- Catherine? - It'll be the first item I bring up in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.40,0:31:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗蘭克  先按兵不動  別聯繫馮\NFrank, stay put for now. But don't contact Feng.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.81,0:31:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也是  雷蒙德\NAnd that goes for you, too, Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.13,0:32:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,建橋的事談妥之前不許你們再私下會面\NI don't want any more back-channeling until the bridge is revived.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.24,0:32:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凱瑟琳  有什麼事直接和我說\NAnd, Catherine, you communicate directly with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.46,0:32:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的  先生\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.27,0:32:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就先說到這裏了\NAll right. We're done here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.78,0:32:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一滴血濺了出來\NThe first drops of blood have been spilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.02,0:32:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,子彈擦過我的臉頰  但我沒有倒下\NBullet grazed my cheek, but I haven't fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.26,0:32:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,道格  想個辦法讓我見到馮\NDoug, find me a way to meet Feng.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.61,0:32:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有件事我們得先談談\NWe need to discuss something first.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.42,0:32:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼了\NWhat's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.39,0:32:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我剛跟一個叫賽斯·格雷森的人通了電話\NI just got off the phone with a guy named Seth Grayson.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.97,0:32:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和我丈夫聊過了\NI've spoken with my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.81,0:32:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,道格說了  感謝你能見我\NDoug told me. Thank you for fitting me in today.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.51,0:32:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是這個吧  -86年8月\N- Is that it? - August '86.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.20,0:32:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們憑什麼相信你\NAnd why should we trust you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.80,0:32:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些證據康納沒能抹去\NThere was evidence that Connor didn't make disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.50,0:32:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我本可以把這個拿給《美國週刊》\NI could've taken this to Us Weekly
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.33,0:32:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,報酬夠我買新房了\Nand bought a new house.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.79,0:32:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可我把它帶來給您\NInstead, I brought it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.22,0:32:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我當時面試的時候你為什麼沒申請\NAnd why didn't you apply when I was interviewing candidates?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.41,0:32:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,申請了也沒用  薇拉不喜歡我\NThere's no point. Willa doesn't like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.19,0:32:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她怕我\NI intimidate her.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.49,0:32:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這日記就是我的簡歷\NThat journal is my version of a resume.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.26,0:32:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是勒索信\NOr extortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.90,0:33:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我沒想勒索您  安德伍德夫人\NI'm not extorting you, Mrs. Underwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.25,0:33:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是想強調\NI'm just highlighting the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.14,0:33:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的決定和正確決定的差別\Nbetween a good choice and the right choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.60,0:33:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你說解雇剛聘用三個月的媒體主管\NAnd tell me, how would we handle the repercussions
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.09,0:33:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所帶來的影響我們要怎麼應對\Nof firing our comm director three months after we hire him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.14,0:33:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您不用解雇他\NYou don't fire him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.93,0:33:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您告訴他僱用我是為了減輕工作量\NYou tell him that you're bringing me on board to help with the workload.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.78,0:33:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他還負責您  我負責您丈夫\NHe stays on with you. I cover your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.61,0:33:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,康納不會喜歡和我合作的\NConnor will hate working with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.80,0:33:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,過幾個月我再找人來挖他牆角\NI'll arrange a job offer elsewhere in a few months.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.70,0:33:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到那時  他會願意接受的\NBy the time it comes in, he'll want to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.38,0:33:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,康納也知道  如何保證他不會公開\NConnor knows. What's to prevent him from going public?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.13,0:33:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能搞定康納·埃利斯\NI can handle Connor Ellis.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.68,0:33:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您只能相信我  我...\NYou just have to take me on my word on that. I –
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.28,0:33:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只知道\NHere's what I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.85,0:33:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您要弄垮我比我扳倒您容易得多\NIt is far easier for you to destroy me than the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.53,0:33:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得和我丈夫談談\NI have to speak to my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.06,0:33:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒問題\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.13,0:34:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我沒有複印\NI didn't make any copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.72,0:34:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您手上的是唯一的一份\NYou have the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.24,0:34:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,純尊尼獲加黑牌\NUh, Johnny Walker Black, neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.02,0:34:35.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-東西在哪  -我口袋裏\N- Where is it? - It's in my pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.96,0:34:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,給我吧\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.35,0:34:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有問題嗎  -沒有  一切就緒\N- Something up? - No. We're good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.06,0:34:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看起來很緊張\NYou seem nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.65,0:34:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雖然我干了二十年違法亂紀的事\NJust because I've been breaking the law for 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.58,0:34:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我還是會覺得緊張\Ndoesn't mean I don't still get nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.28,0:34:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-嘉文  -別說我的名字\N- Gavin. - Do not say my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.37,0:34:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看著我\NLook at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.58,0:35:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒問題的  我們練習過了\NIt's gonna be fine. We practiced.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.40,0:35:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有信心  會成功的\NI'm confident. This is gonna work.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.78,0:35:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我請你\NI got your drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.63,0:35:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他非常有資歷\NHe's more than qualified.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.93,0:35:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的直覺怎麼說\NWhat do your instincts tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.32,0:35:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想再增加曝光度了\NThat I just don't wanna end up more exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.97,0:35:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格雷森都知道了\NWell, Grayson already knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.50,0:35:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們要是不表現出...\NI mean, if we don't exhibit some degree of --
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.19,0:35:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓道格去查查他\NHave Doug look into him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.82,0:35:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看我們有沒有籌碼\NLet's see if there's some leverage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.72,0:35:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我們不知道他能查到什麼\NYeah, but we don't know what he'll find
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.00,0:35:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什麼時候能查到  這期間格雷森又會做什麼\Nor when,  or what he'll do in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.28,0:35:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這讓我們無從防備\NAnd that puts us into unchartered territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.56,0:35:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我們解雇康納  他也會告密的\NWell, Connor will expose us, too, if we let him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.15,0:35:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,處理得好就不會\NNot if it goes smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.75,0:36:02.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果現在拒絕格雷森  我們無法預料後果\NIf we turn away Grayson now, we can't predict anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.45,0:36:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且他可比我們要輸得起\NAnd, look, he has a lot less to lose than we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.12,0:36:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  我只是不相信他  弗蘭西斯\NOkay. I just – I don't think we can trust him, Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.27,0:36:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果康納盡了職我們也不會有這麻煩了\NWe wouldn't be having this conversation if Connor had done his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.09,0:36:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我寧可要個不可信任的手下\NAnd I'd rather manage someone I don't trust
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.77,0:36:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也不要做事不周到的\Nthan someone who is reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.76,0:36:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  下一步怎麼做\NFine. What's the next step?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.40,0:36:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我先親自跟格雷森談談\NI'd like to talk to Grayson myself first,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.40,0:36:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然後我讓道格跟康納談談\Nand then I'll have Doug talk to Connor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.74,0:36:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你那邊怎麼樣\NHow are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.36,0:36:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你關注新聞了嗎\NYou been following the news?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.82,0:36:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,對我們來說是好是壞\NIs it bad for us? Or good?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.52,0:36:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都有可能\NCould go either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.87,0:36:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要我的話就開口\NI'm here if you need me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.32,0:36:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我明天就回去\NI'm back tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.12,0:36:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我愛你  -我也愛你\N- I love you. - Love you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.33,0:36:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-都準備好了嗎  -都準備好了  先生\N- We all set? - All set, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.58,0:36:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走吧\NLet's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.21,0:37:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  把燈關掉\NOh, no, no. Turn those off.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.72,0:37:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把燈關掉\NTurn those off.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.78,0:37:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在哪\NWhere is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.76,0:37:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這邊走  先生\NRight this way, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.85,0:37:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奧古斯都會拉小提琴嗎\NDid Augustus play?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.44,0:37:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望我會\NI like to think I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.84,0:38:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你自己的名字是什麼\NWhat's your own name?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.86,0:38:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在這裏的時候  我就是奧古斯都·安德伍德\NWhen I'm here, I'm Augustus Underwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.80,0:38:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的真名是什麼\NWhat's your real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.19,0:38:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你覺得這不真實嗎\NDoesn't this feel real to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.39,0:38:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能帶我去看他死的地方嗎  具體地點\NWill you show me where he died? The exact spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.93,0:38:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的  先生\NI will, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.21,0:38:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去向我的祖先致敬\NI'm gonna pay respects to my ancestor.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.33,0:38:25.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請給我點隱私\NI would appreciate a little privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.37,0:38:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們在這裏等著\NWe'll wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.90,0:38:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小約翰在移動\NLittle John on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.51,0:38:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就在那些樹後\NJust beyond those trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.70,0:38:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝你  我自己過去吧\NThank you. I'll be good from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.88,0:38:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒事\NWe're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.50,0:39:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你沒等太久\NI hope you haven't waited long.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.75,0:39:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這裏很平靜  我不介意\NIt's peaceful here. I didn't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.44,0:39:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在很平靜  但有一萬五千人曾在這裏喪生\NPeaceful now. Fifteen thousand men died in these woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.88,0:39:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的曾曾曾祖父死在我們站的地方\NMy grandfather's grandfather died where we're standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.35,0:39:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的祖父在革命中犧牲\NMy grandfather was killed in the Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.47,0:39:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我聽說了\NSo I've heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.44,0:39:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怕死嗎  副總統先生\NDo you fear death, Mr. Vice President?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.57,0:39:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟其他人一樣\NNo more or less than any man.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.11,0:39:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,死亡給我激勵  讓我去經歷一切\NIt motivates me. To experience everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.77,0:39:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在一切化為糞土之前  努力成就偉業\Naccomplish all I can before it all vanishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.88,0:39:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在這方面我覺得我們很像\NI think you and I are similar in that regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.57,0:39:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我們為什麼要彼此背道而馳呢\NThen why are we working at cross purposes?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.33,0:39:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的意思是\NNow what you mean is,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.35,0:39:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為什麼我不服從你和塔斯克先生\N"Why am I not submitting to you and Mr. Tusk?"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.02,0:39:42.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在破壞談判\NYou're sabotaging the negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.71,0:39:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而你在利用談判達到自己的目的\NAnd you're using them for your own personal ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.73,0:39:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,錯了  我花了七年時間說服常委\NWrong. It's taken me seven years to convince the Standing Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.11,0:39:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這才是應該採取的做法\Nthat this was the right course of action.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.69,0:39:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以給你和塔斯克帶來數十億收益的做法\NA course of action that will earn you and Tusk billions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.42,0:39:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你約我在這裏見面就為了攻擊我嗎\NWhy did you want this meeting? Just to attack me?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.51,0:39:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為了給雷蒙德帶個信\NTo send a message to Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.83,0:40:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美國總統和我不是他的傀儡\NThe President of the United States and I are not his puppets.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.82,0:40:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就這麼跟他說\NNow you tell him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.38,0:40:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  橋的事沒戲了  沒有挽回餘地\NFine. The bridge deal is dead. There will be no saving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.95,0:40:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,隨你怎麼折騰吧\NStick a knife through its heart and put an apple in its mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.02,0:40:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我才不在乎呢\NI won't shed a tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.47,0:40:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們總統會把失敗歸咎於你\NYour President will ascribe the failure to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.77,0:40:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我願意冒這個險\NI'll take the risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.03,0:40:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好想想  副總統先生\NThink strategically, Mr. Vice President.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.76,0:40:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你這是把我們往絕路上推\NYou're setting us on a very dangerous course.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.15,0:40:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道格蘭特將軍是如何擊敗李將軍的嗎\NDo you know how Grant defeated Lee?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.07,0:40:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的人更多  僅此而已\NHe had more men. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.97,0:40:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且他願意讓他們去送死\NAnd he was willing to let them die.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.72,0:40:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是屠殺  而非策略  贏得了戰爭\NIt was butchery, not strategy, which won the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.78,0:40:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塔斯克先生和我有豐厚資源可以利用\NMr. Tusk and I have great resources at our disposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.87,0:40:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你們的錢加起來\NAdd up all your billions together,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.16,0:40:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相當於斯洛伐克的國內生產總值\Nand you get the GDP of Slovakia.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.32,0:40:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我背後是美利堅合眾國的聯邦政府\NI have the federal government of the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.19,0:40:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們的錢嚇不倒我\NYour money doesn't intimidate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.21,0:40:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你最多能買到影響力\NThe most that you can buy is influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.06,0:40:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我可以利用憲法施壓\NBut I wield Constitutional authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.87,0:41:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最強大的軍隊並不總是能取勝\NThe strongest army doesn't always win.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.61,0:41:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毛主席從幾千人的軍隊起步\NMao started out with only a few thousand men.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.91,0:41:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最終打下了半個亞洲\NThey took over half a continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.97,0:41:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毛主席已經死了  他的中國也死了\NMao is dead. And so is his China.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.63,0:41:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我沒死\NBut I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.30,0:41:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,目前還沒有\NNot yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.04,0:41:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別忘了  你的祖先為戰敗的一方而戰\NDon't forget. Your ancestor fought for the losing side.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.35,0:41:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成者王  敗者寇\NThere is no sacred ground for the conquered.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.38,0:41:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們這裏有九千餘台服務器  分屬幾百家客戶\NWe have over 9,000 servers here, utilized by several hundred clients.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.06,0:41:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,從小企業到大公司都有\NEverything from small businesses to major corporations.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.84,0:41:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最大的客戶都有誰\NWhat are some of the largest clients?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.41,0:41:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這裏最大的是美國電話電報公司\NThe largest here is AT&T.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.51,0:41:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們的服務器佔了這層大半的空間\NTheir servers occupy more than half of the floor space.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.97,0:41:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能讓我看看嗎\NAnd can you show me?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.90,0:41:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,當然\NI am.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.79,0:42:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這邊走\NRight this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.28,0:42:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你昨晚有沒有去見馮\NDid you or did you not meet with Feng last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.79,0:42:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這話從何說起  雷蒙德\NWhere is this coming from, Raymond?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.44,0:42:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回答我  弗蘭克\NAnswer the question, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.26,0:42:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上次談話後我就沒聯繫過他了  總統先生\NI have not contacted him since you and I spoke, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.50,0:42:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完全按照您的要求\NJust as you instructed me to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.17,0:42:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,馮可不是這麼說的\NNot according to Feng.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.57,0:42:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是也不許見他嗎  雷蒙德\NI believe you were also instructed to avoid him too, Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.33,0:42:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他自己找上門來的  我只是接了電話\NHe reached out to me. I just answered the call.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.28,0:42:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們事先有明確的協議  弗蘭克\NWe had clear, prearranged terms, frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.33,0:42:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,私下接觸了數月\NMonths of back-channeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.92,0:42:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在第一線  總統先生\NI am on the front lines, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.68,0:42:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的親身體會是\NAnd I can tell you firsthand
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.17,0:42:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們現在面對的這個國家\Nthat we are dealing with a regime
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.56,0:42:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不僅有事隱瞞\Nthat is not being forthright and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.34,0:42:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且會利用任何風吹草動\Nwill seize upon the faintest whiff of trepidation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.53,0:42:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是次考驗\NThis is a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.74,0:42:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看我們被逼到什麼境地會投降\NTo see how far they can push us before we break.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.40,0:42:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別讓他們得逞  中止談判\NDo not play their game. End the talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.91,0:42:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不能反應過度\NWe can't overreact here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.50,0:42:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們中止了商貿聯委會的談判\NWell, they walked away from the Joint Commission.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.94,0:42:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們也可以中止峰會\NWe can walk away from the Summit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.26,0:43:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,經濟損失難以估量  市場會\NThe economic fallout would be catastrophic. The market would--
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.07,0:43:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要麼向這個新興超級大國卑躬屈膝也行\NOr we can just kowtow and submit to the new reigning superpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.66,0:43:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,別誇大其詞  弗蘭克\NDon't be hyperbolic, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.34,0:43:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們可是在跟全球四分之一的人口打交道\NWell, we are dealing with one quarter of the world's population.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.00,0:43:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生  這會釀成大錯的\NMr. President, you would be making a disastrous mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.42,0:43:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你到底效忠誰  雷蒙德\NWhere are your allegiances, Raymond?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.11,0:43:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是馮山德還是美國\NWith Xander Feng or to the United --?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.78,0:43:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎麼敢質疑我的\NDon't you dare question me about --
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.72,0:43:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行了  安靜\NAll right. Silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.83,0:43:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我犯了兩個錯誤\NThere were two mistakes. Both of them mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.15,0:43:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一個錯誤是允許你  雷蒙德\NThe first was allowing you, Raymond,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.21,0:43:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓你的商業夥伴參與談判\Nto enlist your business partner for these talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.26,0:43:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是想\NI was simply trying to --
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.12,0:43:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而第二個錯誤就是讓你去  弗蘭克\NAnd the second was enlisting you, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.29,0:43:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不但沒把話說清楚\NInstead of clarity,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.19,0:43:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還造成誤解  外交表現糟糕\Nwe got miscommunication. That's poor diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.28,0:43:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生  聽我說\NMr. President, listen --
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.57,0:43:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  你們的話我都聽過了\NOh, no. I've listened. To both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.67,0:43:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但只聽到了互相譴責\NAnd all I've heard is accusations.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.46,0:43:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你們誰都不願負責  那我來\NNow if neither of you will take responsibility, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.00,0:43:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們撤出\NWe're pulling out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.52,0:43:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,並非是聽從你的意見  弗蘭克\NThat's not because you suggested it, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.13,0:43:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是因為你協商失敗\NIt's because you've made such a mess of these negotiations
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.31,0:43:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓我不得不表現出強硬態度\Nthat I have no other choice than a show of strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.68,0:43:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們兩個都讓我很失望\NYou've both disappointed me greatly.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.77,0:43:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統先生\NMr. President --
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.06,0:43:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統已離線\NThe President has left the call.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.42,0:44:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德  你還在嗎\NRaymond, are you still there?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.61,0:44:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這是他二十年來第一次\NThat's the first time he's ever hung up on me
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.02,0:44:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,掛我電話\Nin 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.55,0:44:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,為你難過\NOh. I feel for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.95,0:44:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再見  弗蘭克\NGoodbye, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.39,0:44:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,現在  殺戮開始\NAnd the butchery begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.97,0:44:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,從這排起  到後面七排全是\NIt's all the way down this row and the next seven rows over.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.75,0:44:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想進去看看  是吧\NNow you wanted to see inside one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.69,0:44:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  那就太好了\NYeah, that would be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.75,0:44:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,進去吧\NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.37,0:44:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其實沒什麼好看的\NThere's not much to it, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.84,0:44:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是一堆硬盤和電線\NJust a lot of hard drives and wires.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.15,0:44:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,說到文件備份  如果突然停電\NSo in terms of back-up, if the power goes down,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.22,0:44:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比如碰上自然災害\Nsome natural disaster hits,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.64,0:44:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,龍捲風或地震之類的  要怎麼\Nlike a storm, or an earthquake, what exactly --?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.29,0:44:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-趴在地上  -不許動\N- On the ground. - Freeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.38,0:44:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不  我  -立刻趴下\N- No, no, I  - right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.18,0:44:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-趴下  立刻趴下  -我說了趴下\N- On the ground! On the ground now! - I said on the fucking ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.89,0:45:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我同車回特區吧\NWhy don't you ride back to D.C. with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.74,0:45:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們有事要談\NWe need to discuss something.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.05,0:45:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎麼了\NWhat's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.73,0:45:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們車裏談\NWe'll talk about it in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.76,0:45:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天  我們在陸路戰役遊客中心破土動工\NToday, we break earth on the Overland Campaign Visitors Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.22,0:45:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這樣我們的後代\NSo that generations to come
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.31,0:45:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能深刻體會這片聖地的重要意義\Nwill fully absorb the importance of this hallowed ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.62,0:45:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,銘記這片戰役打響的荒野\Nthe wilderness where the campaign commenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.89,0:45:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奧古斯都  請你來好嗎\NAugustus. Would you do the honor?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.32,0:45:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,請為逝者默哀祈禱\NAnd now a moment of silence and prayer for the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.48,0:46:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,謝謝各位\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.86,0:46:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天祐美國\NAnd God bless the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.35,0:46:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,剛收到消息\NI just heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.29,0:46:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們抓到盧卡斯·古德溫了\NWe got Lucas Goodwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.57,0:47:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}"人民幣被刻意低估"是長期困擾中美經貿關係的一個焦點議題\N多年來  美國國會一直指責中國政府刻意壓低人民幣幣值\N使中國產品價格低廉  出口後佔據價格優勢\N許多議員將美國的對華的巨大貿易逆差  美國國內製造業的蕭條\N均歸咎於人民幣幣值的被低估\N在這個問題上立場最強硬的是國會中的民主黨議員\N他們背後大多有美國工會的支持\N很多議員家鄉有大量從事製造業的選民\N過去這些年  美國國會通過聽證會和立法等多種形式\N向中國政府施壓  該問題也是中美經濟事務會談爭論的焦點
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.57,0:47:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}但白宮在匯率問題上的立場要軟得多\N小布什政府一直頂住國會的壓力  拒絕將中國政府列為"匯率操縱國"\N奧巴馬雖然在競選時接受了工會的巨額捐款\N但上任後也沒有在這個問題上滿足國會的強硬要求\N白宮非常清楚地認識到  如果在這一問題上同中國硬碰硬\N導致貿易戰  其結果將是兩敗俱傷\N所以本屆美國政府一直拒絕公開將中國列為"匯率操縱國"\N2005年中國進行匯率改革之後  人民幣一直穩中有升\N中美之間的匯率問題也逐漸降溫  一些美國智庫的專家認為\N即使美國現在決定到世貿組織就這一問題向中國提起訴訟\N比起5年前來  勝訴的可能性也非常之小

